Package sealey.javafxinventorysystem

Class MainWindow

java.lang.Object
sealey.javafxinventorysystem.MainWindow
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class MainWindow extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
The MainWindow controller controls the components of the initial scene and acts as the "home page" for the application.
Author:
Max Sealey

    • filterParts

      private javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> filterParts()
      The filterParts() method checks a string and returns a list of Parts whose name contains the string, and/or whose ID is equal to the string.
      Returns:
      ObservableList of Parts containing all parts whose name contains the search parameter and/or whose id is equal to the search parameter, or list of all Parts.

    • filterProducts

      private javafx.collections.ObservableList<Product> filterProducts()

      Returns:
      ObservableList of Products containing all products whose name contains the search parameter and/or whose id is equal to the search parameter, or list of all Products.

    • onActionDeletePart

      void onActionDeletePart(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      The onActionDeletePart() event handler deletes the selected part(s) when delete button is clicked. If an item is not selected or deleted, a dialog box displays an error message.
      Parameters:
      event - ActionEvent object for the Delete button

    • onActionDeleteProduct

      void onActionDeleteProduct(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      The onActionDeleteProduct() event handler deletes the selected product(s) when delete button is clicked. If an item is not selected or deleted, a dialog box displays an error message. Won't let you delete a product with any associated parts.
      Parameters:
      event - Delete button event

    • onActionExit

      void onActionExit(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      The onActionExit() event handler closes the application when exit button is clicked and user confirms with alert.
      Parameters:
      event - Exit button event

    • onActionModifyPart

      void onActionModifyPart(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      The onActionModifyPart() event handler sets the ModifyPart scene when the Modify Button under the parts table is clicked. If item is selected, sends part's data to ModifyPart controller.
      Parameters:
      event - Modify button event
      Throws:
      IOException - Throws error message if there is an issue with the event

    • onActionModifyProduct

      void onActionModifyProduct(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      The onActionModifyProduct() event handler sets the ModifyProduct scene when the Modify Button under the products table is clicked. If item is selected, sends selected product's data to Modify Product controller.
      Parameters:
      event - ActionEvent object for the Modify button
      Throws:
      IOException - Throws error message if there is an issue with the event

    • displayData

      Parameters:

      products - ObservableList of products to be displayed in Products table

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Called when MainWindow controller is initialized. It displays all products currently in the inventory, and then sets event listeners on the search bar TextFields. When the search field is selected and the 'enter' button is clicked, the event handler is fired and the table is updated.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - location used to resolve relative paths for the root object, or null
      resourceBundle - resources used to localize root object or null
